Welcome to the website for Introduction to R Programming!
This website contains course materials and outside resources for an introductory R programming course.
Website Content
The Schedule section provides a schedule of topics and links to supplemental resources.
The Resources heading lists several helpful resources for R learners. R for Data Science will serve as the primary text for this course. It’s available for free online, but well-worth the cost for the paper copy.
Most of the course content is listed under the Modules heading. Each module has several components (lecture slides, R code, Summary files) in a pop-out menu.
The Glossary heading provides a definitions of important concepts and functions in R.
Acknowledgements
This course was developed and is maintained by Graham Eglit and was built using the distill package.
